">We generally welcome additional measures to reduces fraudulent or exaggerated claims.</span></li><li style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">However, we do not accept that the problem is as widespread as the </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">insurance industry would have you believe. We do believe that any action to tackle the issue, should be mirrored by measures to protect genuine claimants from some of the more extreme delaying and frustration tactics of insurers and their representatives</span></li></ol><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">P</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">art </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Three</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline"> – </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">The Small Claims Track Threshold</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">To be clear, it is our view that raising the small claims limit would be wrong.</span></li><li style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">main argument</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt"> for change seems perverse: saving the defendant’s costs? The purpose of civil litigation is to provide the wronge</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">d party with an appropriate opportunity to seek proper redress. It is not to provide the culprit with an opportunity to avoid cost. </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">We understand that there is a need for value for money in the administration of justice, but this should not trump the victi</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">m’s rights. </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">There is a very simple way for the perpetrators of RTAs to reduce their costs, and that is to drive with more care, and cause fewer accidents.</span></li><li style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">However, notwithstanding that, your reasoning is flawed. Clever, well-prepared, well-organised and we</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">ll-funded fraudsters may well thrive in an environment where they no longer have to pas</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt"> the first test of persuading their own solicitor </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">of the validity of their </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">claim; Genuine claimants who are disadvantaged by language, disability, ignorance of the proc</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">ess</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt"> or other factors may well fare less well.</span></li><li style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">Government should also exercise extreme caution when basing decisions on data from the MoJ:CMR. Whilst reported turnover from CMCs and associated authorisation renewals may well be down, these are more than com</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">pensated for by the increase in ABS conversions, where, for instance, CMCs and insurance companies have formed their own vehicles for promoting </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">personal injury claims</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt"> outside of the CMR regime, and </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">respective </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">turnover and case volumes will </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">therefore </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">not fe</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">ature in this data. The AA’s ‘AA Law’ ABS, accounting for </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">more than </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">10,000 claims p.a. </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">from</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt"> approximately 1 million policy holders </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt"> a case in point: This volume and turnover has simply exited the CMR data and compliance regime, but represents a sizeable </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">chunk of the RTA market nonetheless.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Part </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Four</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline"> – </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">The </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">W</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">hiplash </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">I</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">ssue and </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Data S</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">haring</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">We understand (but do not agree) that </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">government</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt"> feel it is beneficial to society to dissuade people from claiming for damages when they have suffered whiplash. That it is</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt"> also beneficial to insurers is irrelevant and is no reason to form policy and legislation.</span></li><li style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">If there was any evidence that the insurance industry could be trusted to pass on savings to policyholders in the form of reduced premiums, or indeed to report the </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">make-up of its pricing transparently, there might be some merit in seeking to let victims bear a greater burden of the cost of litigation, but there is none. Insurance premium pricing bears very little relation to what is happening in the market, nor does </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">it reflect experience or customer loyalty. Any consumer who has bought a policy at, say £400 via a price comparison site, and then received a renewal quote for £600 at the end of an accident-free year </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">of driving </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">will attest to this.</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt"> In light of this, the g</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">overnment must exercise extreme caution in legislating with the promise of reduced premiums whispered in its ears; despite the stats the ABI will present, the average driver will not </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">witness</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt"> any </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">substantive </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">saving any time soon.</span></li><li style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt">There are tools which could</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt"> potentially assist with the identification of fraudulent claimants by claimant solicitors, specifically Netfoil, access to which as we understand it is restricted. An opening up of access to such tools to all members of the personal injury marketplace can</span><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt"> only be beneficial, and the government should seek to apply pressure to facilitate this.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'DIN Mittelschrift Std'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Dece</span><a name="_Go